00:29:16.840 --> 00:29:19.426
Well. we've got quite the collective here.
don't we?

500
00:29:22.513 --> 00:29:23.679
Who are you?

501
00:29:23.680 --> 00:29:25.264
I'm the step-grandfather.

502
00:29:25.265 --> 00:29:26.557
Did I ask you to stand?

503
00:29:26.558 --> 00:29:28.310
Uh… [clears throat]

504
00:29:29.895 --> 00:29:31.271
And those two back there.

505
00:29:32.231 --> 00:29:34.524
Those are the two sex worker colleagues
you subpoenaed?

506
00:29:34.525 --> 00:29:37.068
- [Lawrence] They are. Your Honor.
- There is no law

507
00:29:37.069 --> 00:29:39.570
that disqualifies sex workers
from being parents.

508
00:29:39.571 --> 00:29:43.534
Your Honor.
our argument is more about the totality.

509
00:29:44.034 --> 00:29:47.954
the sex work. the drug addict grandfather.
the vicious grandmother.

510
00:29:47.955 --> 00:29:49.539
- May I speak?
- [chuckles] Please.

511
00:29:49.540 --> 00:29:50.998
- No. Jinx--
- This-This person has

512
00:29:50.999 --> 00:29:52.583
- demeaned my family.
- Jinx. I have… Jinx!

513
00:29:52.584 --> 00:29:54.294
- [Shyanne] Sit down.
- [exhales heavily]

514
00:29:59.675 --> 00:30:01.260
- Bring the child in here.
- [Lace] Yes.

515
00:30:03.470 --> 00:30:05.388
Dad. you can't just jump up.

516
00:30:05.389 --> 00:30:07.139
He has to call on you.

517
00:30:07.140 --> 00:30:10.811
This isn't a ring where you get
to leap in off the turnbuckle.

518
00:30:11.979 --> 00:30:13.604
[door opens]

519
00:30:13.605 --> 00:30:15.732
[tense music playing]

520
00:30:18.277 --> 00:30:19.278
Step right up here.

521
00:30:22.906 --> 00:30:25.616
- You are the roommate?
- Yes. yeah.

522
00:30:25.617 --> 00:30:27.369
Uh. and this is little Bodhi.

523
00:30:35.752 --> 00:30:37.171
- [babbles]
- [Susie gasps]

524
00:30:38.130 --> 00:30:39.923
- [giggles]
- [gasps]

525
00:30:42.968 --> 00:30:44.344
Hand the baby to his mother. please.

526
00:30:45.804 --> 00:30:47.055
[Margo sighs]

527
00:30:48.265 --> 00:30:50.641
- [Bodhi cooing. giggling]
- Here's Mama.

528
00:30:50.642 --> 00:30:54.146
[chuckles. sighs]

529
00:30:55.647 --> 00:30:58.733
- [giggling continues]
- [chuckles]

530
00:30:58.734 --> 00:31:02.403
And the village. the family unit which
the petitioner disparages in his papers.

531
00:31:02.404 --> 00:31:05.324
- This here is the village?
- Yes. sir.

532
00:31:06.700 --> 00:31:07.993
Pass the baby to the grandfather.

533
00:31:09.286 --> 00:31:12.497
- [Bodhi coos. babbles]
- [sniffles. exhales heavily]

534
00:31:17.336 --> 00:31:18.462
Hey. little man.

535
00:31:19.546 --> 00:31:20.631
What's going on?

536
00:31:21.381 --> 00:31:25.219
- [Bodhi giggling]
- [Jinx] What's going on? [chuckles]

537
00:31:26.094 --> 00:31:28.555
[growls]

538
00:31:29.139 --> 00:31:30.307
Pass the baby to the grandmother.

539
00:31:33.477 --> 00:31:36.313
[Bodhi babbles]

540
00:31:39.274 --> 00:31:42.986
- [babbling]
- Hey.

541
00:31:45.155 --> 00:31:46.156
[chuckles]

542
00:31:50.953 --> 00:31:52.996
[Bodhi whines]

543
00:31:57.709 --> 00:31:59.544
There you go. [breathes shakily]

544
00:31:59.545 --> 00:32:01.046
[Bodhi babbling]

545
00:32:01.672 --> 00:32:04.757
- Hey… Hi. Hi.
- [babbling continues]

546
00:32:04.758 --> 00:32:06.259
[Shyanne sobbing]

547
00:32:06.260 --> 00:32:08.303
[tender music playing]

548
00:32:10.472 --> 00:32:11.473
Hi.

549
00:32:12.307 --> 00:32:13.308
Hi. baby.

550
00:32:14.268 --> 00:32:16.186
[Bodhi giggles]

551
00:32:16.895 --> 00:32:18.730
- What's with the tears?
- [sniffles]

552
00:32:20.566 --> 00:32:23.777
Hay fever. [chuckles. sobs]

553
00:32:24.778 --> 00:32:26.238
Take the boy to his father.

554
00:32:28.073 --> 00:32:29.532
[sniffles] Okay.

555
00:32:29.533 --> 00:32:30.826
[chuckles]

556
00:32:31.869 --> 00:32:33.035
[sobs. sniffles]

557
00:32:33.036 --> 00:32:34.830
[tense music playing]

558
00:32:40.711 --> 00:32:43.380
[breathing shakily]

559
00:32:48.385 --> 00:32:49.928
- [grunts]
- [Bodhi whines]

560
00:32:51.221 --> 00:32:52.680
[grunts]

561
00:32:52.681 --> 00:32:56.310
[Bodhi whines. wailing]

562
00:32:59.855 --> 00:33:01.106
[huffs]

563
00:33:01.732 --> 00:33:03.442
[crying]

564
00:33:05.110 --> 00:33:07.404
[cooing. babbling]

565
00:33:07.905 --> 00:33:11.324
[Mark sobbing]

566
00:33:11.325 --> 00:33:12.408
And why are you crying?

567
00:33:12.409 --> 00:33:16.038
[breathes shakily]
It's the first time I've held my son.

568
00:33:18.707 --> 00:33:21.376
As I look at her holding him…

569
00:33:22.419 --> 00:33:24.378
[sniffles. gulps] …it could be argued

570
00:33:24.379 --> 00:33:28.800
that my poor judgment
has bestowed an incredible windfall.

571
00:33:30.969 --> 00:33:32.053
To them.

572
00:33:32.054 --> 00:33:34.598
[inhales shakily] To me.

573
00:33:35.891 --> 00:33:37.351
[breathing shakily]

574
00:33:39.353 --> 00:33:40.979
You see me holding him.

575
00:33:42.856 --> 00:33:45.234
Him being held by me.

576
00:33:47.236 --> 00:33:49.737
As a mother holds her child.

577
00:33:49.738 --> 00:33:50.739
[breathes shakily]

578
00:33:52.658 --> 00:33:54.034
This is my son.

579
00:33:54.910 --> 00:33:56.410
[Bodhi coos]

580
00:33:56.411 --> 00:33:57.412
I am his mother.

581
00:33:57.996 --> 00:33:59.413
[breathes shakily]

582
00:33:59.414 --> 00:34:00.666
I am his mother.

583
00:34:23.688 --> 00:34:25.481
This child should know his father.

584
00:34:25.482 --> 00:34:26.816
[attendees murmuring]

585
00:34:26.817 --> 00:34:29.609
Primary custody goes to the mother.
He gets the child two weekends a month.

586
00:34:29.610 --> 00:34:31.737
My clerk will draft
and issue the order. Adjourned.

587
00:34:32.322 --> 00:34:34.616
- [gasps] What just happened?
- What ju… What… What happened?

588
00:34:35.367 --> 00:34:36.868
[whispers] You just won.

589
00:34:36.869 --> 00:34:38.327
- [gasps. laughing]
- [gasping]

590
00:34:38.328 --> 00:34:39.662
[Lace] You won.

591
00:34:39.663 --> 00:34:41.497
Oh. my baby.

592
00:34:41.498 --> 00:34:43.208
[tender music playing]

593
00:34:46.837 --> 00:34:48.839
[Margo crying] Hi.

594
00:34:49.505 --> 00:34:52.091
Hey. Yeah. [chuckles]

595
00:34:52.092 --> 00:34:54.218
[exclaiming]

596
00:34:54.219 --> 00:34:55.845
- [Shyanne] Are you serious? Oh!
- [chuckles]

597
00:34:55.846 --> 00:34:56.847
[Susie whispers] Good job.

598
00:34:57.806 --> 00:34:59.725
[Shyanne. Margo crying]

599
00:35:00.642 --> 00:35:02.227
- [sniffles]
- Yeah.

600
00:35:03.145 --> 00:35:04.146
Yeah.

601
00:35:09.109 --> 00:35:10.903
I'm actually a really good father.

602
00:35:13.655 --> 00:35:15.489
You'll see once you get to know me.

603
00:35:15.490 --> 00:35:17.950
- [coos]
- [sniffles. chuckles]

604
00:35:17.951 --> 00:35:18.952
That's good.

605
00:35:19.745 --> 00:35:22.539
Because I really do
want you to get to know him.

606
00:35:24.458 --> 00:35:26.335
Now. not later.

607
00:35:29.755 --> 00:35:31.130
This is your dad.

608
00:35:31.131 --> 00:35:33.758
- [chuckles] Hi.
- [cooing]

609
00:35:33.759 --> 00:35:36.220
[sniffles. mumbles]

610
00:35:37.304 --> 00:35:39.806
[chuckles. kisses]

611
00:35:40.516 --> 00:35:43.351
All right. I'm making
my special celebratory lasagna tonight.

612
00:35:43.352 --> 00:35:44.644
- Everybody's invited.
- [cheers]

613
00:35:44.645 --> 00:35:47.188
And I will make my super margaritas.

614
00:35:47.189 --> 00:35:48.272
- Hi.
- Oh. there she is.

615
00:35:48.273 --> 00:35:49.899
- Congratulations! [laughs]
- Congrats.

616
00:35:49.900 --> 00:35:51.025
- Thank you.
- Oh! You won.

617
00:35:51.026 --> 00:35:52.443
- Hi. lil cutie.
- You won.

618
00:35:52.444 --> 00:35:54.820
- You won. Bodhi!
- Yes. you did! You did!

619
00:35:54.821 --> 00:35:56.155
- We did!
- Oh. my gosh.

620
00:35:56.156 --> 00:35:58.115
- That was pretty badass.
- Um. can I just say

621
00:35:58.116 --> 00:36:00.368
you guys… you guys look hot.

622
00:36:00.369 --> 00:36:02.787
Oh… [giggles] …coming from you?

623
00:36:02.788 --> 00:36:04.163
- [both] Thank you.
- Oh.

624
00:36:04.164 --> 00:36:08.752
Uh. by the way.
I never called Child Protective Services.

625
00:36:10.045 --> 00:36:11.046
That wasn't me. [chuckles]

626
00:36:13.549 --> 00:36:14.799
Wow.

627
00:36:14.800 --> 00:36:16.968
They can't just respond
to anonymous complaints.

628
00:36:16.969 --> 00:36:18.846
I mean.
it has to come from a reliable source.

629
00:36:19.805 --> 00:36:23.141
If he didn't do it. then… who?

630
00:36:24.643 --> 00:36:25.853
Who would do that?

631
00:36:28.230 --> 00:36:30.691
I… just as…

632
00:36:32.234 --> 00:36:33.527
as a precaution.

633
00:36:34.111 --> 00:36:35.444
[tense music playing]

634
00:36:35.445 --> 00:36:39.449
Just to make sure Bodhi was safe.

635
00:36:46.290 --> 00:36:50.168
When I saw Jinx
just lying there in that hospital

636
00:36:50.169 --> 00:36:54.380
and everyone just standing around
refusing to hold him to account.

637
00:36:54.381 --> 00:36:57.593
I wasn't looking to cost Margo custody.
of course not.

638
00:36:58.510 --> 00:37:02.346
You brought the cops
into our family business.

639
00:37:02.347 --> 00:37:04.558
You brought me into this family. Shyanne.

640
00:37:06.685 --> 00:37:08.728
Isn't it my job to try to protect them?

641
00:37:08.729 --> 00:37:09.897
Behind my back?

642
00:37:10.439 --> 00:37:12.023
What other choice did I have?

643
00:37:12.024 --> 00:37:15.110
You know. maybe I was
just trying to insulate you from…

644
00:37:16.445 --> 00:37:20.698
Give you the gift of deniability
because you weren't gonna do it.

645
00:37:20.699 --> 00:37:23.827
You were not gonna report Margo. Shyanne.

646
00:37:24.578 --> 00:37:26.079
Because you love her too much.

647
00:37:27.789 --> 00:37:29.416
And you sure
wouldn't have done it to Jinx.

648
00:37:31.919 --> 00:37:33.587
'Cause you love him too much too.

649
00:37:39.343 --> 00:37:41.969
[tender music playing]

650
00:37:41.970 --> 00:37:45.474
[Margo] <i>Margo came from
a messy. complicated clan.</i>

651
00:37:46.850 --> 00:37:53.232
<i>A group of people who loved so completely.
it at times presented as pain.</i>

652
00:37:55.150 --> 00:37:57.986
<i>And her son will
have to grow up in that tangle.</i>

653
00:37:58.862 --> 00:38:03.742
<i>But he will thrive
because what choice does he have?</i>

654
00:38:04.868 --> 00:38:09.121
<i>And he will innately know
that adversity begets love</i>

655
00:38:09.122 --> 00:38:10.874
<i>with a special kind of vigor</i>

656
00:38:11.750 --> 00:38:15.044
<i>that allows you
to trust the ground under your feet</i>

657
00:38:15.045 --> 00:38:20.592
<i>and then launch your ship into the wild.
unknowable sea to seek your fortune.</i>

658
00:38:24.137 --> 00:38:25.305
<i>And maybe…</i>

659
00:38:28.600 --> 00:38:30.560
{\an8}<i>catch yourself a whale.</i>

660
00:38:30.561 --> 00:38:32.145
Cha-ching.

661
00:38:32.855 --> 00:38:35.106
[tender music playing]

662
00:38:35.107 --> 00:38:37.401
[Bodhi cooing]

663
00:38:40.779 --> 00:38:42.614
Good night. my baby.

664
00:38:45.701 --> 00:38:47.703
[sultry pop music playing on speakers]

665
00:39:02.885 --> 00:39:04.094
[Susie] Labor of love.

666
00:39:04.887 --> 00:39:06.220
It's perfect. Susie.

667
00:39:06.221 --> 00:39:07.305
[Susie chuckles]

668
00:39:07.306 --> 00:39:08.891
Oh. And the remote.

669
00:39:10.392 --> 00:39:12.227
- [sighs]
- Whenever you're ready.

670
00:39:14.062 --> 00:39:15.063
I'm ready.

671
00:39:20.402 --> 00:39:22.571
[music continues]

672
00:39:25.032 --> 00:39:26.950
[Margo] <i>I'm the hungry ghost</i>.

673
00:39:28.035 --> 00:39:30.245
[distorted voice]
<i>You crawled into my phone.</i>

674
00:39:30.996 --> 00:39:32.122
<i>You're trapped here.</i>

675
00:39:33.290 --> 00:39:34.291
<i>Forever.</i>

676
00:39:36.084 --> 00:39:37.503
<i>I will eat you all.</i>

677
00:39:38.879 --> 00:39:41.423
<i>There will be no survivors.</i>

678
00:39:48.514 --> 00:39:49.515
[camera shutter clicks]
